00:16:03.067 --> 00:16:09.227
We are still coming down from the elation and euphoria of the genuinely breathtaking experience.

00:16:09.277 --> 00:16:13.067
Life will never quite be the same but we shall visit again and again.”

00:16:14.584 --> 00:16:19.894
and what is perhaps even better than reading the clearly ironic 5* reviews

00:16:20.034 --> 00:16:25.007
from thousands of British pranksters is reading the 1* reviews from people who

00:16:25.224 --> 00:16:29.334
have fallen for it, have travelled there, only to be slightly disappointed.

00:16:30.614 --> 00:16:35.794
Or, as user Debs B put it, in her 1 star review, “I thought this would be

00:16:35.794 --> 00:16:39.374
something special when I was searching for things to see in and around Bude….

00:16:39.754 --> 00:16:45.624
How wrong I was ! Its a Perspex tunnel which was very dirty . It did get me from

00:16:45.644 --> 00:16:49.054
Sainsbury’s car park to the entrance of Sainsbury’s though, without getting wet.

00:16:49.244 --> 00:16:53.384
So one star for that . Don’t bother coming to look , there’s nothing here

00:16:54.514 --> 00:16:58.971
.”
And then she added, “Ps what happened to all the pretty lights as in the pictures

00:17:00.271 --> 00:17:07.411
?“
So, there you have it, five unusual very lighthearted British news stories from 2023.

00:17:08.121 --> 00:17:12.251
From stolen golden toilets to lost sheep, coronation chicken

00:17:12.461 --> 00:17:16.261
